If? Then! Else?
Conditional execution:

if (condition) {
  statement1
}

or

if (condition) {
  statement1
} else {
  statement2
}

Example

x &lt;- 5
if (x &lt; 10) {
  y &lt;- 0
}
y

[1] 0


Another example:

if (x &gt;= 10) {
  y &lt;- 1
} else {
  y &lt;- 0
}
y

[1] 0

Nested if() Statements
if inside an if

if(condition1) {
  if(condition2) {
    statement1 
  } else {
    statement2
  }
}

Adding if else to the descriptives function

my_descriptives &lt;- function(x){
  if(class(x) == "numeric"){
    x.trim &lt;- x[x&gt;0]
    summary(x.trim)
  } else if (class(x) == "factor"){
    x.trim &lt;- droplevels(x[x!=-1])
    table(x.trim)
  }
}
my_descriptives(data$Ages)

   Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
  23.00   36.75   43.00   45.71   53.50   71.00 

my_descriptives(data$Sex)

